WEBVTT

00:00.325 --> 00:05.406
A mini vehicle the size of a small suitcase is taken for a spin by its owner in China.

00:06.017 --> 00:09.631
The fully functioning mini car is 60 centimeters in length,...

00:09.722 --> 00:13.953
...35 centimeters in width and 40 centimeters in height.

00:14.858 --> 00:19.546
Xu Zhiyun, a 60-year-old Shanghai resident, takes great pride in his creation.

00:22.663 --> 00:26.187
The vehicle has nightlights and turn signals that are automatic,...

00:26.365 --> 00:28.477
...following the direction of the steering wheel.

00:28.859 --> 00:32.517
It also has a sound system, which can be controlled remotely.

00:32.875 --> 00:35.891
With a top speed of just over 12 miles per hour...

00:35.999 --> 00:39.957
...it apparently only needs four liters of petrol to run a day.

00:40.167 --> 00:42.699
Xu spent two years making the vehicle,...

00:42.817 --> 00:46.580
...using mostly spare parts he collected from car repair shops.

